## 🚀 Quick Start

### Prerequisites
- Node.js 18+ installed
- npm or yarn package manager

### Installation

Dependencies are already installed. Just run:

```bash
npm run dev
```

This will:
1. Start Vite dev server (frontend) on an available port (tries 5183-5190)
2. Auto-detect which port Vite started on
3. Start Electron app with the correct port
4. Spawn Express backend on port 3000
5. Open desktop window with hot reload

**Smart Port Detection:** The dev script automatically finds an available port between 5183-5190, so you can run multiple desktop apps simultaneously without port conflicts!

