## 🧭 Routing & Navigation

### HashRouter for Electron

This app uses **React Router's HashRouter** instead of BrowserRouter because Electron loads pages using the `file://` protocol, which doesn't support traditional URL-based routing.

**Key Points:**
- ✅ **Use `useNavigate()` hook** - Never use `window.location.href` or `<a href>` for internal navigation
- ✅ **Relative paths work** - Use `/user/profile` instead of full URLs
- ✅ **Hash-based URLs** - Routes appear as `file:///path/to/app.html#/user/profile`
- ❌ **Avoid window.location** - Causes full page reloads and breaks app state

### Navigation Best Practices

```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT - Use useNavigate hook
import { useNavigate } from 'react-router-dom';

function MyComponent() {
  const navigate = useNavigate();

  return (
    <Button onClick={() => navigate('/user/profile')}>
      Go to Profile
    </Button>
  );
}

// ❌ WRONG - Don't use window.location
function BadComponent() {
  return (
    <Button onClick={() => window.location.href = '/user/profile'}>
      Go to Profile
    </Button>
  );
}

// ❌ WRONG - Don't use <a> tags for internal navigation
function BadComponent2() {
  return <a href="/user/profile">Profile</a>;
}
```

### Role-Based Navigation

The app implements role-based access control with three levels:
- **Admin Roles:** `admin.tenant`, `admin.org`, `admin.system`
- **Moderator Roles:** `moderator.review`, `moderator.approve`, `moderator.manage`
- **User Roles:** `user.basic`, `user.pro`, `user.max`

```tsx
import { hasRole } from '@/shared/utils';

// Check single role
if (hasRole(user, ['admin.system'])) {
  // Show admin features
}

// Check multiple roles
if (hasRole(user, ['admin.tenant', 'admin.org', 'admin.system'])) {
  // Show features for any admin
}
```

### Route Helper Utility

The `route()` helper ensures consistent routing across the app:

```tsx
import { route } from '@/shared/utils';

// Use in navigation
navigate(route('/user/admin'));

// No longer needed for navigation, but available if needed
// Previously used with window.location.href (deprecated pattern)
```

