## 💾 Database & First-Run Setup

### First-Run Setup Wizard

When you build and distribute the application, users will see a **Setup Wizard** on first launch to create their admin account securely.

**Production Flow:**
1. User launches the app for the first time
2. Setup wizard automatically appears
3. User creates admin account with custom credentials
4. Database is initialized with their account
5. User is redirected to login page

**Development Flow:**
The database is automatically initialized on first run. The schema is applied via better-sqlite3 migrations.

**Important Security Notes:**
- ✅ **Production:** Uses setup wizard (unique credentials per installation)
- ❌ **Never ship pre-bundled database** (all users would have same credentials)
- 🔒 **Database excluded from build** (configured in package.json)
- 📁 **User data stored in:** `app.getPath('userData')` directory

### Test User Accounts

During development, you can create test accounts via the setup wizard or authentication endpoints:

**Example User Roles:**

| Role | Level | Full Permission |
|------|-------|----------------|
| admin | system | `admin.system` - System Administrator (full access) |
| admin | org | `admin.org` - Organization Admin |
| admin | tenant | `admin.tenant` - Tenant Admin |
| moderator | manage | `moderator.manage` - Moderator Manager |
| moderator | approve | `moderator.approve` - Moderator Approver |
| moderator | review | `moderator.review` - Moderator Reviewer |
| user | max | `user.max` - Max User |
| user | pro | `user.pro` - Pro User |
| user | basic | `user.basic` - Basic User |

### Database Schema

The User table is defined in `src/desktop/main/lib/db-client.ts`:

```sql
CREATE TABLE IF NOT EXISTS User (
  id INTEGER PRIMARY KEY AUTOINCREMENT,
  email TEXT NOT NULL UNIQUE,
  password TEXT NOT NULL,
  name TEXT,
  phone TEXT,
  role TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'user',
  level TEXT NOT NULL DEFAULT 'basic',
  tenantId TEXT,
  isVerified INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 0,
  isActive INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT 1,
  lastLogin INTEGER,
  resetToken TEXT,
  resetTokenExpiry INTEGER,
  verificationToken TEXT,
  verificationExpiry INTEGER,
  createdAt INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT (strftime('%s', 'now') * 1000),
  updatedAt INTEGER NOT NULL DEFAULT (strftime('%s', 'now') * 1000)
);
```

