## 🐛 Troubleshooting

### All Ports Busy (5183-5190)
If all ports are in use, the script will show an error. Free up a port:
```bash
# Kill a specific port
npx kill-port 5183
npm run dev
```

### Backend Port Already in Use
```bash
npx kill-port 3000
npm run dev
```

### Module Not Found
```bash
rm -rf node_modules package-lock.json
npm install
```

### Backend Not Responding
```bash
# Check health endpoint
curl http://localhost:3000/health

# Restart Electron
npm run dev
```

### Navigation Not Working

If clicking links doesn't navigate properly:

**Check 1: Using HashRouter**
```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT in App.tsx
import { HashRouter as Router } from 'react-router-dom';

// ❌ WRONG - Don't use BrowserRouter in Electron
import { BrowserRouter as Router } from 'react-router-dom';
```

**Check 2: Using useNavigate**
```tsx
// ✅ CORRECT
const navigate = useNavigate();
<Button onClick={() => navigate('/path')}>Go</Button>

// ❌ WRONG - Don't use window.location
<Button onClick={() => window.location.href = '/path'}>Go</Button>
```

**Check 3: Import Path Aliases**
```tsx
// ✅ Works in this project
import { route } from '@/shared/utils';
import { route } from '../../../../shared/utils';
```

### Database Issues

```bash
# Reset database completely (removes all data)
rm database/dev.db

# Restart app to recreate database
npm run dev
```

