## 🏗️ Architecture Decisions

### Why HashRouter?

**Problem:** Electron loads pages using `file://` protocol, which doesn't support standard URL paths.

**Solution:** Use HashRouter to handle routing via URL hash fragments (`#/path`).

```tsx
// src/desktop/renderer/App.tsx
import { HashRouter as Router } from 'react-router-dom';

<Router future={{ v7_startTransition: true, v7_relativeSplatPath: true }}>
  <AuthProvider>
    <UserProvider>
      <PageRouter />
    </UserProvider>
  </AuthProvider>
</Router>
```

### Why useNavigate() Hook?

**Problem:** `window.location.href` causes full page reloads, losing React state and breaking HashRouter.

**Solution:** Use React Router's `useNavigate()` hook for client-side navigation.

```tsx
// ✅ All admin pages updated to use this pattern
import { useNavigate } from 'react-router-dom';

const navigate = useNavigate();
navigate('/user/admin/show?id=123');  // Client-side navigation
```

### Why Relative Paths in HTML?

**Problem:** Absolute paths (`/favicon.svg`) don't work with `file://` protocol.

**Solution:** Use relative paths (`./favicon.svg`) in index.html.

```html
<!-- src/desktop/renderer/index.html -->
<link rel="icon" type="image/svg+xml" href="./favicon.svg" />
<script type="module" src="./main.tsx"></script>
```

### Role-Based Access Control

**Design:** Hierarchical permission system with `role.level` format.

```typescript
// User roles follow: role.level
'admin.system'      // Highest level - full system access
'admin.org'         // Organization-level admin
'admin.tenant'      // Tenant-level admin
'moderator.manage'  // Can manage content
'moderator.approve' // Can approve content
'moderator.review'  // Can review content
'user.max'          // Premium user features
'user.pro'          // Professional user features
'user.basic'        // Standard user access
```

**Permission Checking:**
```tsx
// src/desktop/renderer/shared/utils/role.ts
export const hasRole = (user: { role: string; level: string } | null, allowedRoles: string[]): boolean => {
  if (!user || !allowedRoles.length) return true;
  const userPermission = `${user.role}.${user.level}`;
  return allowedRoles.includes(userPermission);
};
```

### Feature-Based Component Architecture (FBCA)

**Frontend Structure:**
```
src/desktop/renderer/features/
├── auth/              # Authentication feature
│   ├── pages/         # Auto-discovered routes
│   ├── components/    # Feature-specific components
│   ├── context/       # Auth context provider
│   └── config/        # Auth configuration
├── user/              # User management feature
│   ├── pages/
│   │   └── admin/     # Admin sub-routes
│   ├── components/
│   ├── context/       # User context provider
│   └── types/         # TypeScript types
└── main/              # Main/landing feature
    └── pages/
```

**Backend Structure:**
```
src/desktop/main/features/
├── auth/
│   └── auth.route.ts    # Auto-discovered as /api/auth/*
├── user/
│   └── user.route.ts    # Auto-discovered as /api/user/*
├── setup/
│   └── setup.route.ts   # Auto-discovered as /api/setup/*
└── welcome/
    └── welcome.route.ts # Auto-discovered as /api/welcome/*
```

**Benefits:**
- ✅ Auto-discovery - Add files, routes automatically available
- ✅ Colocation - Related code stays together
- ✅ Scalability - Easy to add/remove features
- ✅ Team collaboration - Features can be developed independently

